KIM-OS is a minimal Operating System for MCUs.

KIM means "Keep It Minimal".

Documentation is "work in progress" under the doc/ subfolder; it is written
in reST/Sphinx. Type make doc from root folder, to get the pdf version.

A compiled pdf is provided for ease of use: doc/kim-os.pdf

You can also just browse into the source code and pick up whatever you're
interested in: unless otherwise stated inside a file, everything here is
released under MIT-style license. See COPYING and LICENSE for details.
